block.comment: Resets score and number of rows. Causes start button to appear. Speed is a general "difficulty variable" controlling the speed of the aliens, lasers and base. The variable increases as aliens are destroyed and as the level increases.
Sets up aliens and barricades for the start of each level.
Resets conditions to level 1.
Prevents more than 4 rows of aliens due to performance issues. Changes speed value. Smaller speed makes the the glide time less and thus aliens move faster.
Ensures clones are cleaned up before next level starts.
Watches for laserbeam to hit baricade. Keeps track of how many times its hit and changes costumes to give visual feedback.
This block ensures clones will be cleaned up before the next level starts.
Initializes clone
Variable used to control direction of motion. Bounds variables set left and right bounds for each clone.
Checks if score is making use of the digit. Then sets scoredigit to correct value that corresponds to the correct costume.

scripts.comment: Sets the digit to the correct location when the game begins.

block.comment: This block sets the initial location and size for the clone. Then uses the speed variable to glide the clone off the screen.
Ensures that extra clones are cleaned up before next level starts.
Checks for collision with the barricade.
Simply checks for a mouse click to proceed to the next level.
Creates clone of missle. Reloading variables prevents constant firing and causes a wait time. Couldn't use "timer" as that was used by alien clones - there only seemed to be one timer...
Watches for command to fire and checks if the base is reloaded.
Checks for collision with laser
Checks for mouse click then initializes game.
Both if statements evaluate if the alien is beyond the bounds and if so switches direction.
Watches for missle to touch alien
Updates list of active aliens. Used for determining who can shoot.
Checks for winning condition.
Checks if the alien below exists. If not then alien will have a chance to fire.

scripts.comment: Timer prevents constant firing. Random number adds randomness to whether a shot is fired so that firing is not simply time based.

block.comment: Checks that base is within bounds. Then uses arrow keys to control motion. If base is beyond bounds it returns the base to within bounds

custom-block.comment: K controls the number of clusters. i controls the number of rows. j controls the number of columns in each row. Other numbers that are hard coded were chosen to make three clusters fit on the screen.

Creates clones at given positions. Position variables are global and are used by alien clones. Alien list is later used by clones to determine who can fire. The value 1 indicates that the alien is active a value of 0 indicates the alien is not active.
